00:41:46,919 --> 00:41:49,035
Show us what you see.

492
00:41:57,919 --> 00:42:01,195
Keep your nerve. Steady.

493
00:42:01,359 --> 00:42:03,236
Riddikulus !

494
00:42:04,240 --> 00:42:06,117
And next! Step up. step up!

495
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:08,912
Wonderful. wonderful!

496
00:42:22,359 --> 00:42:24,395
Here!

497
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:31,752
Riddikulus !

498
00:42:39,919 --> 00:42:42,717
Right. Sorry about that.
That's enough for today.

499
00:42:42,879 --> 00:42:44,790
Collect your books from the back.

500
00:42:44,960 --> 00:42:47,474
That's the end of the lesson.
Thank you! Sorry!

501
00:42:47,639 --> 00:42:50,551
Sorry. you can have too much
of a good thing.

502
00:42:52,479 --> 00:42:56,870
Remember. these visits to Hogsmeade
village are a privilege.

503
00:42:57,159 --> 00:42:59,878
Should your behavior reflect poorly
on the school...

504
00:43:00,040 --> 00:43:02,838
...that privilege shall not
be extended again.

505
00:43:03,280 --> 00:43:06,431
No permission form signed.
no visiting the village.

506
00:43:06,599 --> 00:43:08,078
That's the rule. Potter.

507
00:43:08,280 --> 00:43:11,352
Those with permission. follow me.
Those without. stay put.

508
00:43:11,520 --> 00:43:13,909
I thought if you signed it.
then I could--

509
00:43:14,079 --> 00:43:16,468
I can't. Only a parent
or a guardian can sign.

510
00:43:16,639 --> 00:43:19,711
Since I am neither.
it would be inappropriate.

511
00:43:21,920 --> 00:43:26,311
I'm sorry. Potter.
That's my final word.

512
00:43:27,479 --> 00:43:30,596
Forget about it. guys. See you later.

513
00:43:43,839 --> 00:43:45,795
Professor. can I ask you something?

514
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:49,675
You want to know why I stopped you
facing that boggart. yes?

515
00:43:49,879 --> 00:43:51,232
I thought it'd be obvious.

516
00:43:51,399 --> 00:43:54,118
I assumed it would take the shape
of Lord Voldemort.

517
00:43:54,280 --> 00:43:57,636
I did think of Voldemort at first.

518
00:43:57,839 --> 00:44:00,353
But then I remembered that night
on the train...

519
00:44:00,519 --> 00:44:02,953
-...and the dementor.
-|'m very impressed.

520
00:44:03,119 --> 00:44:05,872
That suggests what you fear the most
is fear itself.

521
00:44:06,040 --> 00:44:07,473
This is very wise.

522
00:44:07,639 --> 00:44:09,630
Before I fainted...

523
00:44:09,880 --> 00:44:11,791
...I heard something.

524
00:44:12,320 --> 00:44:13,878
A woman...

525
00:44:14,320 --> 00:44:15,594
...screaming.

526
00:44:15,800 --> 00:44:18,917
Dementors force us to relive
our very worst memories.

527
00:44:19,119 --> 00:44:21,917
Our pain becomes their power.

528
00:44:22,719 --> 00:44:24,835
I think it was my mother...

529
00:44:25,000 --> 00:44:27,116
...the night she was murdered.

530
00:44:28,679 --> 00:44:32,957
The very first time I saw you. Harry.
I recognized you immediately.

531
00:44:33,519 --> 00:44:36,238
Not by your scar. by your eyes.

532
00:44:36,639 --> 00:44:38,709
They're your mother. Lily's.

533
00:44:39,599 --> 00:44:40,998
Yes.

534
00:44:41,320 --> 00:44:44,198
Oh. yes. I knew her.

535
00:44:46,440 --> 00:44:50,115
Your mother was there for me
at a time when no one else was.

536
00:44:50,320 --> 00:44:53,392
Not only was she
a singularly gifted witch...

537
00:44:53,560 --> 00:44:56,757
...she was also
an uncommonly kind woman.

538
00:44:57,240 --> 00:45:00,198
She had a way of seeing
the beauty in others...

539
00:45:00,359 --> 00:45:06,275
...even. and most especially. when that
person could not see it in themselves.

540
00:45:07,679 --> 00:45:10,273
And your father. James.
on the other hand...

541
00:45:10,439 --> 00:45:11,918
...he....

542
00:45:12,399 --> 00:45:15,596
He had a certain. shall we say.
talent for trouble.

543
00:45:17,800 --> 00:45:23,079
A talent. rumor has it.
he passed on to you.

544
00:45:26,919 --> 00:45:29,752
You're more like them
than you know. Harry.

545
00:45:30,560 --> 00:45:33,552
In time. you'll come to see
just how much.

546
00:45:36,879 --> 00:45:41,077
Honeyduke's Sweetshop is brilliant.
but nothing beats Zonko's Joke Shop.

547
00:45:41,280 --> 00:45:43,714
We never got to go
to the Shrieking Shack.

548
00:45:43,879 --> 00:45:47,758
-You heard it's the most--
-Haunted building in Britain. I know.

549
00:45:49,079 --> 00:45:50,512
What's going on?

550
00:45:50,679 --> 00:45:53,034
Probably Neville forgot
the password again.

551
00:45:53,200 --> 00:45:55,509
-Hey.
-Oh. you're there.

552
00:45:55,679 --> 00:45:59,797
Let me through. please.
Excuse me! I'm Head Boy!

553
00:46:01,359 --> 00:46:02,951
Get back. all of you.

554
00:46:03,119 --> 00:46:06,156
No one is to enter this dormitory
until it's been searched.

555
00:46:06,320 --> 00:46:07,594
The Fat Lady! She's gone!

556
00:46:09,599 --> 00:46:11,954
Serves her right.
She was a terrible singer.

557
00:46:12,120 --> 00:46:13,951
It's not funny. Ron.

558
00:46:15,879 --> 00:46:19,792
Keep calm. everyone. Break into fours.
Back to your common room.

559
00:46:25,879 --> 00:46:26,868
-Be quiet.
-Make way.

560
00:46:27,079 --> 00:46:28,956
-The headmaster's here.
-Come on. move.

561
00:46:29,159 --> 00:46:30,956
You heard. Move!

562
00:46:44,599 --> 00:46:47,352
Mr. Filch? Round up the ghosts.

563
00:46:47,679 --> 00:46:51,592
Tell them to search every painting
in the castle to find the Fat Lady.

564
00:46:51,800 --> 00:46:54,758
There's no need for ghosts. professor.

565
00:46:55,559 --> 00:46:57,595
The Fat Lady's there.

566
00:46:58,399 --> 00:47:00,310
Mind where you're going! Slow down!

567
00:47:00,879 --> 00:47:03,439
You listen! I'm Head Boy!

568
00:47:03,599 --> 00:47:05,908
-Come back here!
-Keep moving!

569
00:47:09,359 --> 00:47:12,112
Dear lady. who did this to you?

570
00:47:13,960 --> 00:47:18,795
Eyes like the devil. he's got.
and a soul as dark as his name.

571
00:47:19,679 --> 00:47:22,557
It's him. headmaster.
The one they all talk about.

572
00:47:22,719 --> 00:47:25,074
He's here. somewhere in the castle!

573
00:47:25,320 --> 00:47:27,390
Sirius Black!

574
00:47:27,599 --> 00:47:32,514
Secure the castle. Mr. Filch.
The rest of you. to the Great Hall.

575
00:47:59,440 --> 00:48:04,150
I've searched the Astronomy Tower
and the Owlery. There's nothing there.

576
00:48:04,320 --> 00:48:06,788
-Thank you.
-The third floor's clear too. sir.

577
00:48:06,960 --> 00:48:08,837
-Very good.
-|'ve done the dungeons.

578
00:48:09,000 --> 00:48:11,560
No sign of Black. nor anywhere else
in the castle.

579
00:48:11,760 --> 00:48:14,149
I didn't really expect him to linger.

580
00:48:15,359 --> 00:48:17,589
Remarkable feat. don't you think?

581
00:48:17,760 --> 00:48:19,955
To enter Hogwarts Castle
on one's own...

582
00:48:20,120 --> 00:48:22,680
-...comp|ete|y undetected?
-Ouite remarkable. yes.

583
00:48:22,879 --> 00:48:24,631
Any theories on how he managed it?

584
00:48:24,839 --> 00:48:27,672
Many. Each as unlikely as the next.

585
00:48:27,920 --> 00:48:29,399
You may recall...

586
00:48:29,560 --> 00:48:32,279
...prior to the start of term
I expressed concerns...

587
00:48:32,440 --> 00:48:34,431
...about your appointment
of Professor--

588
00:48:34,599 --> 00:48:38,512
Not a single professor inside this castle
would help Sirius Black enter it.

589
00:48:38,680 --> 00:48:40,989
I'm quite convinced
the castle is safe...

590
00:48:41,160 --> 00:48:44,630
...and I'm more than willing to send
the students to their houses.

591
00:48:44,800 --> 00:48:47,030
What about Potter?
Should he be warned?

592
00:48:47,240 --> 00:48:49,754
Perhaps. But for now. let him sleep.

593
00:48:50,600 --> 00:48:55,116
For in dreams. we enter a world
that's entirely our own.

594
00:48:55,400 --> 00:49:01,635
Let them swim in the deepest ocean
or glide over the highest cloud.

595
00:49:37,439 --> 00:49:40,636
Turn to page 394.

596
00:49:49,679 --> 00:49:53,115
Excuse me. sir.
Where's Professor Lupin?

597
00:49:53,800 --> 00:49:57,076
That's not really your concern.
is it. Potter?

598
00:49:57,240 --> 00:50:00,949
Suffice it to say your professor
finds himself incapable of teaching...

599
00:50:01,160 --> 00:50:05,995
...at the present time.
Turn to page 394.

600
00:50:10,639 --> 00:50:12,231
“Werewolves“?

601
00:50:12,559 --> 00:50:15,198
Sir. we just learned about red caps
and hinkypunks.

602
00:50:15,439 --> 00:50:18,431
-We're not meant to start that for weeks.
-Ouiet.

603
00:50:18,639 --> 00:50:21,676
When did she come in?
Did you see her come in?

604
00:50:22,280 --> 00:50:25,636
Now. which one of you
can tell me the difference...

605
00:50:25,839 --> 00:50:28,148
...between an Animagus
and a werewolf?

606
00:50:28,840 --> 00:50:30,671
No one?

607
00:50:31,160 --> 00:50:33,958
-How disappointing.
-Please. sir.

608
00:50:34,159 --> 00:50:37,196
An Animagus is a wizard
who elects to turn into an animal.

609
00:50:37,359 --> 00:50:38,838
A werewolf has no choice.

610
00:50:39,240 --> 00:50:40,878
With each full moon...

611
00:50:41,040 --> 00:50:44,749
...he no longer remembers who he is.
He'd kill his best friend.

612
00:50:44,959 --> 00:50:48,395
The werewolf only responds
to the call of its own kind.

613
00:50:49,519 --> 00:50:52,158
Thank you. Mr. Malfoy.
That's the second time...

614
00:50:52,319 --> 00:50:54,549
...you've spoken out of turn.
Miss Granger.

615
00:50:54,719 --> 00:50:56,630
Are you incapable
of restraining yourself...

616
00:50:56,799 --> 00:50:59,996
...or do you take pride
in being an insufferable know-it-all?

617
00:51:00,280 --> 00:51:03,556
-He's got a point. you know.
-Five points from Gryffindor.

618
00:51:03,759 --> 00:51:08,150
As an antidote to your ignorance.
and on my desk. by Monday morning...

619
00:51:08,360 --> 00:51:11,909
...two rolls of parchment
on the werewolf. with emphasis...

620
00:51:12,080 --> 00:51:14,548
-...on recognizing it.
-|t's Ouidditch tomorrow.

621
00:51:15,600 --> 00:51:18,797
Then I suggest you take extra care.
Mr. Potter.

622
00:51:19,000 --> 00:51:22,879
Loss of limb will not excuse you.

623
00:51:23,080 --> 00:51:26,675
Page 394.

624
00:51:28,600 --> 00:51:29,999
The term “werewolf“ . ..

625
00:51:30,880 --> 00:51:35,192
...is a contraction
of the Anglo-Saxon word “wer“...

626
00:51:35,919 --> 00:51:40,151
...which means “man." and “wolf.“
Werewolf. man-wolf.

627
00:51:40,799 --> 00:51:43,029
There are several ways
to become a werewolf.

628
00:51:43,240 --> 00:51:46,118
They include being given the power
of shape-shifting...

629
00:51:46,360 --> 00:51:48,191
...being bitten by a werewolf....

630
00:52:06,239 --> 00:52:09,709
Go. Harry! Go. Harry!

631
00:54:04,600 --> 00:54:07,319
Aresto momentum!

632
00:54:09,479 --> 00:54:12,471
-He looks a bit peaky. doesn't he?
-Peaky?

633
00:54:12,639 --> 00:54:14,834
What do you expect?
He fell over 100 feet.

634
00:54:15,000 --> 00:54:17,753
Let's walk you off a tower
and see what you look like.

635
00:54:17,960 --> 00:54:20,872
Probably a right sight better
than he normally does.

636
00:54:24,399 --> 00:54:27,232
-How are you feeling?
-Oh. brilliant.

637
00:54:27,439 --> 00:54:29,316
You gave us a right good scare.

638
00:54:29,560 --> 00:54:32,916
-What happened?
-Well. you fell off your broom.

639
00:54:33,199 --> 00:54:35,429
Really? I meant the match. Who won?

640
00:54:39,679 --> 00:54:41,317
No one blames you. Harry.

641
00:54:41,519 --> 00:54:45,194
Dementors aren't supposed to be
on the grounds. Dumbledore's furious.

642
00:54:45,400 --> 00:54:47,391
After he saved you.
he sent them off.

643
00:54:47,560 --> 00:54:51,075
There's something else
you should know too.

644
00:54:51,599 --> 00:54:57,674
When you fell. your broom sort of blew
into the Whomping Willow. and....

645
00:54:58,159 --> 00:54:59,592
Well....

646
00:55:00,800 --> 00:55:02,995
I'm sorry to hear
about your broomstick.

647
00:55:03,320 --> 00:55:05,834
Is there no chance of fixing it?

648
00:55:05,999 --> 00:55:07,318
No.

649
00:55:07,480 --> 00:55:10,677
Professor. why do the dementors
affect me so?

650
00:55:11,080 --> 00:55:14,038
-I mean. more than everyone else?
-Listen.

651
00:55:14,199 --> 00:55:17,236
Dementors are the foulest creatures
to walk this earth.

652
00:55:17,439 --> 00:55:21,512
They feed on every good feeling.
every happy memory...

653
00:55:22,040 --> 00:55:26,431
...until a person is left with absolutely
nothing but his worst experiences.

654
00:55:26,639 --> 00:55:30,678
You are not weak. Harry.

655
00:55:30,839 --> 00:55:34,752
Dementors affect you most because
there are true horrors in your past.

656
00:55:34,960 --> 00:55:37,918
Horrors your classmates
can scarcely imagine.

657
00:55:38,359 --> 00:55:40,554
You have nothing to be ashamed of.

658
00:55:40,760 --> 00:55:44,639
-|'m scared. professor.
-|'d consider you a fool if you weren't.

659
00:55:44,799 --> 00:55:48,155
I need to know how to fight them.
You could teach me.

660
00:55:48,320 --> 00:55:50,231
You made the one
on the train go away.

661
00:55:50,439 --> 00:55:52,111
There was only one that night.

662
00:55:52,399 --> 00:55:56,790
-But you made it go away.
-I don't pretend to be an expert. Harry.

663
00:55:57,119 --> 00:56:01,874
But as the dementors seem
to have developed an interest in you...

664
00:56:02,040 --> 00:56:05,555
...perhaps I should teach you.
But after the holidays.

665
00:56:05,719 --> 00:56:07,550
For now. I need to rest.

666
00:56:31,960 --> 00:56:36,078
Last call for Hogsmeade!
Come on. now!

667
00:56:51,039 --> 00:56:52,950
-Guys. let me go.
-C|ever. Harry.

668
00:56:53,120 --> 00:56:55,918
-But not clever enough.
-We've got a better way.

669
00:56:56,079 --> 00:56:58,798
-|'m trying to get to Hogsmeade.
-We know.

670
00:56:58,960 --> 00:57:00,109
We'll get you there.

671
00:57:00,280 --> 00:57:02,874
-We'll show you a quicker way.
-If you pipe down.

672
00:57:03,039 --> 00:57:06,475
-B|ess him.
-Let me go! Come on. guys. Don't--

673
00:57:07,079 --> 00:57:09,547
-Now. Harry.
-Come and join the big boys.

674
00:57:10,920 --> 00:57:12,956
What are you doing?!

675
00:57:13,199 --> 00:57:15,918
-What's this rubbish?
-“What's this rubbish?“ he says.

676
00:57:16,080 --> 00:57:19,277
-|t's the secret to our success.
-|t's a wrench giving it to you--

677
00:57:19,439 --> 00:57:22,237
But we've decided
your needs are greater than ours.

678
00:57:22,399 --> 00:57:24,071
George. if you will.

679
00:57:24,240 --> 00:57:27,391
I solemnly swear
that I am up to no good.

680
00:57:30,879 --> 00:57:34,315
“Messrs. Moony. Wormtail.
Padfoot and Prongs...

681
00:57:34,719 --> 00:57:37,552
...are proud to present
the Marauder's Map.“

682
00:57:37,800 --> 00:57:39,950
We owe them so much.

683
00:57:43,360 --> 00:57:47,035
Hang on. This is Hogwarts.
And that--

684
00:57:47,199 --> 00:57:49,554
-No. Is that really--?
-Dumb|edore.

685
00:57:49,720 --> 00:57:50,994
-In his study.
-Pacing.

686
00:57:51,160 --> 00:57:53,037
Does that a lot.

687
00:57:53,240 --> 00:57:54,992
-So this map shows--
-Everyone.

688
00:57:55,199 --> 00:57:57,110
-Where they are.
-What they're doing.

689
00:57:57,279 --> 00:57:58,348
-Every minute.
-Every day.

690
00:57:58,520 --> 00:58:01,398
-Brilliant! Where did you get it?
-From Filch's office.

691
00:58:01,560 --> 00:58:04,199
-First year.
-There are seven secret passageways...

692
00:58:04,360 --> 00:58:06,920
-...out of the castle.
-We'd recommend this one.

693
00:58:07,079 --> 00:58:10,116
-The One-Eyed Witch passageway.
-Leads you to Honeyduke's.

694
00:58:10,280 --> 00:58:12,032
Hurry. Filch is heading this way.

695
00:58:12,200 --> 00:58:15,476
And don't forget. When you're done.
just give it a tap and say:

696
00:58:15,639 --> 00:58:19,791
“Mischief managed.“
Otherwise. anyone can read it.

697
00:58:53,679 --> 00:58:55,795
Now. how much do you want?

698
00:59:02,800 --> 00:59:04,631
Delicious.

699
00:59:12,319 --> 00:59:16,232
It's meant to be the most haunted
building in Britain. Did I mention that?

700
00:59:16,399 --> 00:59:17,991
Twice.

701
00:59:18,680 --> 00:59:20,910
Do you want to move a bit closer?

702
00:59:21,120 --> 00:59:22,758
To the Shrieking Shack?

703
00:59:23,039 --> 00:59:25,792
Actually. I'm fine here.

704
00:59:25,960 --> 00:59:27,712
Well. well. Look who's here.

705
00:59:28,080 --> 00:59:30,275
You two shopping for your new
dream home?

706
00:59:30,480 --> 00:59:34,598
Bit grand for you. isn't it. Weasle-Bee?
Don't your family sleep in one room?

707
00:59:34,799 --> 00:59:37,871
-Shut your mouth. Malfoy.
-Not very friendly.

708
00:59:38,159 --> 00:59:43,074
Boys. I think it's time we teach
Weasle-Bee how to respect his superiors.

709
00:59:43,279 --> 00:59:46,555
-Hope you don't mean yourself.
-How dare you talk to me!

710
00:59:46,719 --> 00:59:48,630
You filthy little mudblood!

711
00:59:52,680 --> 00:59:54,159
Who is that?

712
01:00:00,119 --> 01:00:02,394
-Don't stand there! Do something!
-What?

713
01:00:21,400 --> 01:00:23,595
What's up. Malfoy? Lost your skis?

714
01:00:27,400 --> 01:00:28,753
Get out of the way!

715
01:00:28,920 --> 01:00:30,478
Move!

716
01:00:30,920 --> 01:00:33,798
Malfoy! Wait! Wait!

717
01:00:37,399 --> 01:00:39,276
Harry!

718
01:00:39,439 --> 01:00:43,318
Bloody hell. Harry.
That was not funny.

719
01:00:44,439 --> 01:00:47,556
Those weasels! Never told me
about any Marauder's Map.

720
01:00:47,759 --> 01:00:51,035
He won't keep it. He'll turn it over
to Professor McGonagall.

721
01:00:51,279 --> 01:00:55,067
-Aren't you?
-Sure. Along with his Invisibility Cloak.

722
01:00:55,240 --> 01:00:57,629
Look who it is. Madam Rosmerta.

723
01:00:57,840 --> 01:01:00,035
-Ron fancies her.
-That's not true!

724
01:01:00,200 --> 01:01:01,997
-Professor McGonagall!
-Corne|ius!

725
01:01:02,159 --> 01:01:03,478
Allow me. minister.

726
01:01:03,679 --> 01:01:05,431
-Oh. Hagrid....
-Sorry about that.

727
01:01:05,639 --> 01:01:08,437
Rosmerta. my dear.
I hope business is good.

728
01:01:08,640 --> 01:01:12,349
It'd be a lot better if the Ministry
wasn't sending dementors...

729
01:01:12,520 --> 01:01:16,399
-...into my pub every other night!
-We have....

730
01:01:16,799 --> 01:01:19,871
-We have a killer on the loose.
-Sirius Black in Hogsmeade!

731
01:01:20,199 --> 01:01:22,554
And what would bring him here?

732
01:01:22,719 --> 01:01:26,712
-Harry Potter.
-Harry Potter?

733
01:01:26,880 --> 01:01:28,552
Come.

734
01:01:31,000 --> 01:01:32,911
Harry!

735
01:01:40,319 --> 01:01:44,597
-No underage wizards allowed in today!
-Shut the damn door!

736
01:01:44,800 --> 01:01:46,711
-So rude.
-Thick heads.

737
01:01:46,959 --> 01:01:48,472
-Thick heads?!
-How dare they!

738
01:01:48,680 --> 01:01:51,717
-Who are they calling thick heads?
-Young whippersnappers!

739
01:01:52,440 --> 01:01:56,194
Nobody will come to a pub where
they'll get scared out of their wits.

740
01:01:56,359 --> 01:02:00,113
Professor Dumbledore doesn't want
dementors around the place.

741
01:02:02,800 --> 01:02:04,518
Tell me what this is all about.

742
01:02:04,679 --> 01:02:08,957
Years ago. when Harry Potter's parents
realized they were marked for death--

743
01:02:09,120 --> 01:02:11,680
Remember? They hid.
Few knew where they were.

744
01:02:11,879 --> 01:02:15,554
One who did was Sirius Black.
And he told You-Know-Who.

745
01:02:15,759 --> 01:02:18,831
Not only did Black lead him
to the Potters that night...

746
01:02:19,000 --> 01:02:22,231
...he also killed Peter Pettigrew!

747
01:02:22,479 --> 01:02:24,549
-Peter Pettigrew?
-Little lump of a boy.

748
01:02:24,719 --> 01:02:26,869
-Always trailing after Black.
-I remember.

749
01:02:27,040 --> 01:02:28,792
Never let James and Sirius
out of his sight.

750
01:02:28,959 --> 01:02:31,598
-What happened?
-Peter tried to warn the Potters...

751
01:02:31,760 --> 01:02:35,753
...and might have. had he not
run into an old friend. Sirius Black.

752
01:02:35,960 --> 01:02:39,635
Black was vicious.
He didn't kill Pettigrew.

753
01:02:39,840 --> 01:02:41,910
He destroyed him!

754
01:02:42,520 --> 01:02:47,071
A finger. That's all that was left.
A finger. Nothing else.

755
01:02:47,240 --> 01:02:50,152
Sirius Black may not have
put his hands to the Potters...

756
01:02:50,319 --> 01:02:53,391
-...but he's the reason they're dead.
-He wants to finish things.

757
01:02:53,600 --> 01:02:56,319
-I don't believe it.
-That's not the worst of it.

758
01:02:56,519 --> 01:03:00,114
-What could be worse?
-This: Sirius Black was...

759
01:03:00,320 --> 01:03:02,356
...and remains to this day...

760
01:03:02,800 --> 01:03:04,358
...Harry Potter's godfather!

761
01:03:12,639 --> 01:03:14,834
Ron. look!

762
01:03:20,319 --> 01:03:22,787
-Sorry. Excuse me. excuse me.
-Merry Christmas.

763
01:03:59,679 --> 01:04:01,431
Harry. what happened?

764
01:04:03,840 --> 01:04:05,876
He was their friend...

765
01:04:06,360 --> 01:04:08,510
...and he betrayed them.

766
01:04:09,279 --> 01:04:11,156
He was their friend!

767
01:04:13,320 --> 01:04:15,197
I hope he finds me.

768
01:04:15,800 --> 01:04:18,030
Because when he does.
I'm gonna be ready!

769
01:04:18,479 --> 01:04:20,993
When he does. I'm gonna kill him!

770
01:04:34,679 --> 01:04:36,237
Harry.

771
01:04:36,719 --> 01:04:38,311
There you are. You came.

772
01:04:38,680 --> 01:04:42,389
Are you sure about this. Harry?
This is very advanced magic...

773
01:04:42,560 --> 01:04:44,915
...well beyond the Ordinary
Wizarding Level.

774
01:04:45,080 --> 01:04:46,559
I'm sure.

775
01:04:47,120 --> 01:04:49,475
Well. everything's prepared.

776
01:04:49,720 --> 01:04:52,951
The spell I'm going to teach you
is called the Patronus Charm.

777
01:04:53,160 --> 01:04:54,559
Did you ever hear of it?

778
01:04:54,719 --> 01:04:56,311
No? Well....

779
01:04:56,479 --> 01:04:59,915
A Patronus is a positive force.
For the wizard who conjures one...

780
01:05:00,079 --> 01:05:04,550
...it works like a shield. with the
dementor feeding on it rather than him.

781
01:05:04,719 --> 01:05:08,394
But in order for it to work.
you need to think of a memory.

782
01:05:08,559 --> 01:05:12,347
Not just any memory. a very happy
memory. a very powerful memory.

783
01:05:12,560 --> 01:05:16,189
Can you do this?
Yes. Very well.

784
01:05:17,360 --> 01:05:19,476
Close your eyes.

785
01:05:21,199 --> 01:05:22,996
Concentrate.

786
01:05:24,200 --> 01:05:26,191
Explore your past.

787
01:05:26,680 --> 01:05:28,477
Do you have a memory?

788
01:05:29,999 --> 01:05:32,115
Allow it to fill you up.

789
01:05:32,800 --> 01:05:34,791
Lose yourself within it.

790
01:05:35,120 --> 01:05:40,240
Then speak the incantation.
Expecto Patronum.

791
01:05:40,639 --> 01:05:43,358
-Expecto Patronum.
-Very good.

792
01:05:47,000 --> 01:05:50,197
Shall we? Wand at the ready.

793
01:06:07,000 --> 01:06:09,798
Expecto Patronum!

794
01:06:10,239 --> 01:06:13,754
Expecto.... Expecto....

795
01:06:13,999 --> 01:06:15,637
Expect. . . .

796
01:06:17,560 --> 01:06:21,473
Here we go. Come on.
Sit up. Deep breaths.

797
01:06:21,759 --> 01:06:25,388
It's all right. I didn't expect you
to do it the first time.

798
01:06:25,800 --> 01:06:30,715
That would have been remarkable.
Here. eat this. You'll feel better.

799
01:06:31,520 --> 01:06:34,273
-That's one nasty dementor.
-Oh. no. no. no.

800
01:06:34,479 --> 01:06:37,118
That was a boggart. Harry.
A boggart.

801
01:06:37,279 --> 01:06:40,316
The real thing would be worse.
Much. much worse.

802
01:06:40,479 --> 01:06:42,993
As a matter of interest.
what were you thinking?

803
01:06:43,160 --> 01:06:46,709
-Which memory did you choose?
-The first time I rode a broom.

804
01:06:47,879 --> 01:06:51,076
That's not good enough.
Not nearly good enough.

805
01:06:57,679 --> 01:07:02,707
There's another.
It's not happy. exactly.

806
01:07:04,559 --> 01:07:06,595
Well. it is.

807
01:07:06,760 --> 01:07:09,228
It's the happiest I've ever felt...

808
01:07:09,399 --> 01:07:13,187
-...but it's complicated.
-|s it strong?

809
01:07:17,400 --> 01:07:20,119
Then let's give it a try. You feel ready?

810
01:07:21,840 --> 01:07:23,512
Just do it.

811
01:07:33,160 --> 01:07:36,277
Expecto Patronum!

812
01:07:37,480 --> 01:07:41,268
Expecto Patronum!

813
01:08:01,999 --> 01:08:03,034
Yes!

814
01:08:04,919 --> 01:08:08,195
Well done. Harry. Well done!

815
01:08:08,720 --> 01:08:12,679
-I think I've had enough for today.
-Yes. Sit down. Here.

816
01:08:12,840 --> 01:08:15,149
Eat this. it helps. It really helps.

817
01:08:15,320 --> 01:08:17,038
And just so you know. Harry...

818
01:08:17,200 --> 01:08:21,034
...I think you'd have given your father
a run for his money. And that...

819
01:08:21,199 --> 01:08:23,155
...is saying something.

820
01:08:25,239 --> 01:08:27,150
I was thinking of him.

821
01:08:27,320 --> 01:08:29,390
And Mum.

822
01:08:29,560 --> 01:08:31,710
Seeing their faces.

823
01:08:32,319 --> 01:08:34,913
They were talking to me.

824
01:08:35,080 --> 01:08:37,230
Just talking.

825
01:08:37,400 --> 01:08:39,630
That's the memory I chose.

826
01:08:41,200 --> 01:08:43,555
I don't even know if it's real.

827
01:08:44,040 --> 01:08:46,110
But it's the best I have.

828
01:08:54,959 --> 01:08:57,189
-Beautifu| day.
-Gorgeous.

829
01:08:57,359 --> 01:08:59,270
Unless you've been ripped to pieces!

830
01:08:59,439 --> 01:09:01,748
Ripped to pieces?
What are you talking about?

831
01:09:01,920 --> 01:09:04,957
-Rona|d has lost his rat.
-I haven't lost anything!

832
01:09:05,119 --> 01:09:07,155
-Your cat killed him!
-Rubbish.

833
01:09:07,319 --> 01:09:10,516
Harry. you've seen the way
that bloodthirsty beast of hers...

834
01:09:10,680 --> 01:09:14,434
...is always lurking about.
And Scabbers is gone.

835
01:09:14,600 --> 01:09:17,353
Well. maybe you should
take better care of your pets!

836
01:09:17,520 --> 01:09:19,511
-Your cat killed him!
-Did not.

837
01:09:19,679 --> 01:09:21,112
-Did.
-Didn't.

838
01:09:23,079 --> 01:09:25,593
How did it go. Hagrid? The hearing?

839
01:09:25,759 --> 01:09:28,910
Well. first off. the committee members
took turns...

840
01:09:29,079 --> 01:09:31,639
...talking about why we were there.

841
01:09:33,439 --> 01:09:35,999
I got up and did my piece.
Said how Buckbeak...

842
01:09:36,160 --> 01:09:38,993
...was a good hippogriff.
always cleaned his feathers.

843
01:09:39,200 --> 01:09:42,112
And then Lucius Malfoy got up.
Well. you can imagine.

844
01:09:42,280 --> 01:09:45,352
He said Buckbeak was a deadly
and dangerous creature...

845
01:09:45,519 --> 01:09:48,431
...who would kill you
as soon as look at you.

846
01:09:48,640 --> 01:09:50,358
And then?

847
01:09:51,040 --> 01:09:53,634
And then he asked for the worst.
did old Lucius.

848
01:09:53,800 --> 01:09:57,759
-They're not sacking you!
-No. I'm not sacked.

849
01:09:59,760 --> 01:10:02,638
Buckbeak's been sentenced to death!

850
01:10:28,319 --> 01:10:33,712
Spiders! There's-- There's spiders.
Spiders. They want me to tap-dance.

851
01:10:33,919 --> 01:10:36,353
-I don't wanna tap-dance!
-Te|| those spiders.

852
01:10:36,559 --> 01:10:40,347
Right. yeah. Tell them. I'll tell them....

853
01:10:57,760 --> 01:10:59,830
-Peter Pettigrew?
-Little lump of a boy.

854
01:10:59,999 --> 01:11:02,991
-Always trailing alter Sirius Black.
-Elaclr was vicious.

855
01:11:03,200 --> 01:11:05,555
He didn 't kill Pettigre w,
he destroyed him!

856
01:11:13,320 --> 01:11:16,630
-Put that light out!
-Sorry.

857
01:11:58,119 --> 01:12:02,078
-Watch it there. boy.
-We're trying to sleep here!

858
01:12:09,959 --> 01:12:12,427
Mischief managed. Nox.

859
01:12:14,560 --> 01:12:15,834
Potter.

860
01:12:15,999 --> 01:12:19,355
What are you doing
wandering the corridors at night?

861
01:12:19,519 --> 01:12:20,634
I was sleepwalking.

862
01:12:20,799 --> 01:12:23,233
How extraordinarily like your father
you are. Potter.

863
01:12:23,399 --> 01:12:27,950
He. too. was exceedingly arrogant.
strutting about the castle.

864
01:12:28,159 --> 01:12:32,311
My dad didn't strut. And nor do I.

865
01:12:33,040 --> 01:12:35,998
If you don't mind. I would appreciate
it if you could lower your wand.

866
01:12:39,400 --> 01:12:41,152
Turn out your pockets.

867
01:12:42,759 --> 01:12:45,273
Turn out your pockets!

868
01:12:48,079 --> 01:12:49,637
What's this?

869
01:12:49,799 --> 01:12:52,916
-Spare bit of parchment.
-Rea|ly? Open it.

870
01:12:59,160 --> 01:13:02,755
Reveal your secrets.

871
01:13:06,399 --> 01:13:07,798
Read it.

872
01:13:10,160 --> 01:13:15,439
“Messrs. Moony. Wormtail. Padfoot.
and Prongs...

873
01:13:15,599 --> 01:13:19,558
...offer their compliments
to Professor Snape and....“

874
01:13:19,839 --> 01:13:21,272
Go on.

875
01:13:22,399 --> 01:13:26,108
“And request he keep his large nose
out of other people's business.“

876
01:13:26,320 --> 01:13:28,754
-You insolent little--
-Professor!

877
01:13:30,320 --> 01:13:32,914
Well. well. Lupin.

878
01:13:33,079 --> 01:13:37,595
Out for a little walk
in the moonlight. are we?

879
01:13:38,920 --> 01:13:41,229
Harry. are you all right?

880
01:13:41,440 --> 01:13:43,795
That remains to be seen.

881
01:13:44,600 --> 01:13:48,195
I have now just confiscated
a rather curious artifact.

882
01:13:48,359 --> 01:13:51,749
Take a look. Lupin.
Supposed to be your area of expertise.

883
01:13:51,920 --> 01:13:56,516
-C|early. it's full of dark magic.
-I seriously doubt it. Severus.

884
01:13:56,680 --> 01:14:00,036
It looks as though it's a parchment
designed to insult anyone...

885
01:14:00,199 --> 01:14:03,908
...who tries to read it.
I suspect it's a Zonko product.

886
01:14:04,079 --> 01:14:08,152
Nevertheless. I shall investigate
any hidden qualities it may possess.

887
01:14:08,319 --> 01:14:11,311
It is. after all. as you say.
my area of expertise.

888
01:14:11,480 --> 01:14:14,677
Harry. would you come with me.
please? Professor. good night.

889
01:14:20,440 --> 01:14:23,079
Are you deaf? Put that light out!

890
01:14:27,960 --> 01:14:29,359
Come in.

891
01:14:31,079 --> 01:14:36,073
I haven't the faintest idea how this map
came to be in your possession...

892
01:14:36,239 --> 01:14:40,551
...but quite frankly. I am astounded
that you didn't hand it in.

893
01:14:40,720 --> 01:14:44,235
Did it never occur to you that this.
in the hands of Sirius Black...

894
01:14:44,400 --> 01:14:46,311
...is a map to you?

895
01:14:47,119 --> 01:14:49,474
-No.
-No. sir.

896
01:14:51,399 --> 01:14:54,311
Your father never set much store
by the rules either.

897
01:14:54,479 --> 01:14:58,631
But he and your mother
gave their lives to save yours.

898
01:14:59,239 --> 01:15:03,152
Gambling their sacrifice
by wandering the castle unprotected...

899
01:15:03,319 --> 01:15:07,597
...with a killer on the loose
seems to me a poor way to repay them!

900
01:15:07,800 --> 01:15:09,870
Now. I will not cover up for you again.

901
01:15:10,040 --> 01:15:12,395
-Do you hear me?
-Yes. sir.

902
01:15:12,560 --> 01:15:16,075
I want you to return to your dormitory
and stay there.

903
01:15:16,239 --> 01:15:20,790
And don't take any detours.
If you do. I shall know.

904
01:15:25,280 --> 01:15:29,512
Professor. just so you know.
I don't think that map always works.

905
01:15:30,360 --> 01:15:35,115
Earlier. it showed someone in the castle.
Someone I know to be dead.

906
01:15:35,519 --> 01:15:38,158
Oh. really? And who might that be?

907
01:15:38,320 --> 01:15:39,799
Peter Pettigrew.

908
01:15:42,319 --> 01:15:44,310
That's not possible.

909
01:15:45,480 --> 01:15:47,072
It's just what I saw.

910
01:15:49,800 --> 01:15:51,438
Good night. professor.

911
01:15:54,800 --> 01:15:58,793
Broaden your minds.
You must look beyond.

912
01:15:58,959 --> 01:16:04,158
The art of crystal gazing
is in the clearing of the Inner Eye.

913
01:16:04,319 --> 01:16:07,516
Only then can you see. Try again.

914
01:16:08,039 --> 01:16:10,030
Now. what do we have here?

915
01:16:12,279 --> 01:16:14,395
Do you mind me trying?

916
01:16:16,720 --> 01:16:19,553
The Grim. possibly.

917
01:16:21,640 --> 01:16:25,553
My dear. from the first moment
you stepped foot in my class...

918
01:16:25,720 --> 01:16:29,349
...I sensed that you did not possess
the proper spirit...

919
01:16:29,519 --> 01:16:33,273
...for the noble art of Divination.
No. you see. there.

920
01:16:33,440 --> 01:16:36,955
You may be young in years.
but your heart is as shriveled...

921
01:16:37,120 --> 01:16:40,954
...as an old maid's. your soul
as dry as the pages of the books...

922
01:16:41,119 --> 01:16:44,111
...to which you so desperately cleave.

923
01:16:59,000 --> 01:17:00,911
Have I said something?

924
01:17:05,399 --> 01:17:10,189
She's gone mental. Hermione has.
Not that she wasn't always mental...

925
01:17:10,360 --> 01:17:12,828
...but now it's in the open
for everyone to see.

926
01:17:12,999 --> 01:17:15,069
Hang on.

927
01:17:15,279 --> 01:17:18,032
-We better take this back.
-|'m not going back.

928
01:17:18,359 --> 01:17:21,635
-Fine. See you later.
-See you.

929
01:17:57,839 --> 01:18:02,913
Harry Potter. . . .

930
01:18:09,519 --> 01:18:13,592
-Professor Trelawney--
-He will return tonight.

931
01:18:13,760 --> 01:18:15,318
Sorry?

932
01:18:15,519 --> 01:18:19,956
Tonight, he who betrayed his friends.
whose heart rots with murder...

933
01:18:20,120 --> 01:18:22,076
...shall break free.

934
01:18:22,240 --> 01:18:24,390
Innocent blood shall be spilt...

935
01:18:24,559 --> 01:18:30,316
...and servant and master
shall be reunited once more.

936
01:18:36,399 --> 01:18:39,516
I'm so sorry. dear boy.
Did you say something?

937
01:18:40,280 --> 01:18:41,998
No.

938
01:18:42,440 --> 01:18:43,919
Nothing.

939
01:19:34,360 --> 01:19:38,239
I can't believe they're going to kill
Buckbeak. It's just too horrible.

940
01:19:38,399 --> 01:19:41,038
-It just got worse.
-What did I say? Father said...

941
01:19:41,200 --> 01:19:45,193
...I can keep the hippogriff's head.
I'll donate it to the Gryffindors' room.

942
01:19:45,360 --> 01:19:47,715
This is going to be rich.

943
01:19:47,920 --> 01:19:49,990
-Look who's here.
-Come to see the show?

944
01:19:50,159 --> 01:19:53,151
You! You foul. loathsome.
evil little cockroach!

945
01:19:53,320 --> 01:19:54,992
Hermione. no!

946
01:19:55,560 --> 01:19:57,710
He's not worth it.

947
01:20:11,239 --> 01:20:13,195
Malfoy. are you okay?

948
01:20:13,400 --> 01:20:17,439
-Let's go. Ouick.
-Not a word to anyone. understood?

949
01:20:17,600 --> 01:20:21,832
-That felt good.
-Not good. brilliant.

950
01:20:40,480 --> 01:20:44,598
Look at him. Loves the smell of the trees
when the wind blows through them.

951
01:20:44,760 --> 01:20:46,955
Why don't we just set him free?

952
01:20:47,119 --> 01:20:49,428
They'd know it was me.
and then Dumbledore...

953
01:20:49,600 --> 01:20:52,478
...would get into trouble.
He's coming down. Dumbledore.

954
01:20:52,640 --> 01:20:54,915
Says he wants to be with me
when they....

955
01:20:55,880 --> 01:20:57,836
When it happens.

956
01:20:58,000 --> 01:20:59,274
Great man. Dumbledore.

957
01:21:00,239 --> 01:21:01,718
A great man.

958
01:21:04,080 --> 01:21:06,958
-We'l| stay with you too.
-You'll do no such thing!

959
01:21:07,120 --> 01:21:10,157
Think I want you seeing
something like that? No.

960
01:21:10,319 --> 01:21:13,834
You just drink your tea and be off.
Oh. Before you do. Ron....

961
01:21:20,960 --> 01:21:23,235
Scabbers! You're alive!

962
01:21:23,399 --> 01:21:26,948
-Keep a closer eye on your pet.
-I think you owe someone an apology.

963
01:21:27,119 --> 01:21:30,714
Right. Next time I see Crookshanks.
I'll let him know.

964
01:21:30,880 --> 01:21:31,915
I meant me!

965
01:21:32,599 --> 01:21:34,715
Blimey. What was that?

966
01:21:40,919 --> 01:21:42,272
Hagrid!

967
01:21:44,119 --> 01:21:45,393
Oh. crikey.

968
01:21:46,799 --> 01:21:49,438
No. minister. Over this way.

969
01:21:49,640 --> 01:21:53,553
It's late. It's nearly dark.
You shouldn't be here.

970
01:21:53,719 --> 01:21:57,348
Someone sees you outside
this time of night. you'll be in trouble.

971
01:21:57,520 --> 01:22:00,956
Particularly you. Harry.
With you in a moment!

972
01:22:02,319 --> 01:22:04,628
Ouick. Ouick!

973
01:22:04,799 --> 01:22:06,471
Hagrid.

974
01:22:06,640 --> 01:22:10,394
-|t'|| be fine. It'll be okay.
-Go on. go on!

975
01:22:12,160 --> 01:22:14,833
