Come on. let's kill him!

1032
01:28:25,519 --> 01:28:28,033
-Wait!
-I did my waiting!

1033
01:28:28,200 --> 01:28:30,509
Twelve years of it!

1034
01:28:31,120 --> 01:28:33,395
In Azkaban!

1035
01:28:42,479 --> 01:28:44,151
Very well. Kill him.

1036
01:28:44,720 --> 01:28:48,315
But wait one more minute.
Harry has the right to know why.

1037
01:28:48,479 --> 01:28:49,992
I know why.

1038
01:28:50,200 --> 01:28:52,350
You betrayed my parents.

1039
01:28:52,519 --> 01:28:55,317
-You're the reason they're dead!
-No. it wasn't him.

1040
01:28:55,479 --> 01:28:57,310
Somebody did betray your parents...

1041
01:28:57,479 --> 01:29:00,835
...somebody who. until quite recently.
I believed to be dead!

1042
01:29:01,039 --> 01:29:04,349
-Who was it. then?
-Peter Pettigrew!

1043
01:29:04,519 --> 01:29:07,511
And he's in this room! Right now!

1044
01:29:07,999 --> 01:29:10,832
Come out. come out. Peter!

1045
01:29:10,999 --> 01:29:13,877
-Come out. come out and play!
-Expelliarmusl

1046
01:29:16,720 --> 01:29:19,109
Vengeance is sweet.

1047
01:29:19,279 --> 01:29:21,429
How I hoped I'd be the one
to catch you.

1048
01:29:21,599 --> 01:29:22,873
Severus--

1049
01:29:23,039 --> 01:29:27,590
I told Dumbledore you were helping a
friend into the castle. Here's the proof.

1050
01:29:27,760 --> 01:29:29,034
Brilliant. Snape.

1051
01:29:29,200 --> 01:29:33,398
You've put your keen mind to the task
and come to the wrong conclusion.

1052
01:29:33,599 --> 01:29:36,159
If you'll excuse us.
Remus and I have business...

1053
01:29:36,319 --> 01:29:41,109
-...to attend to.
-Give me a reason. I beg you!

1054
01:29:41,280 --> 01:29:43,748
-Don't be a fool.
-He can't help it. It's habit.

1055
01:29:43,959 --> 01:29:45,472
-Be quiet.
-Be quiet yourself!

1056
01:29:45,640 --> 01:29:47,949
You two. quarrelling
like an old married couple.

1057
01:29:48,120 --> 01:29:50,554
Run along and play with
your chemistry set!

1058
01:29:51,080 --> 01:29:53,469
I could do it. you know.

1059
01:29:53,920 --> 01:29:59,313
But why deny the dementors?
They're so longing to see you.

1060
01:29:59,480 --> 01:30:02,074
Do I detect a flicker of fear?
Oh. yes.

1061
01:30:02,239 --> 01:30:05,595
A Dementor's Kiss. One can only
imagine what that must be like.

1062
01:30:05,760 --> 01:30:10,959
It's said to be nearly unbearable
to witness. but I'll do my best.

1063
01:30:11,160 --> 01:30:13,310
Severus. please.

1064
01:30:14,319 --> 01:30:16,230
After you.

1065
01:30:20,480 --> 01:30:22,152
Exp elliarm us!

1066
01:30:23,840 --> 01:30:27,276
-Harry! What did you just do?
-You attacked a teacher!

1067
01:30:27,479 --> 01:30:29,947
-Tell me about Peter.
-He was at school with us.

1068
01:30:30,119 --> 01:30:31,711
We thought he was our friend!

1069
01:30:31,880 --> 01:30:34,758
-No. Pettigrew's dead. You killed him!
-No. he didn't.

1070
01:30:34,920 --> 01:30:37,992
I thought so too. until you mentioned
Pettigrew on the map!

1071
01:30:38,199 --> 01:30:40,872
-The map was lying. then.
-The map never lies!

1072
01:30:41,040 --> 01:30:44,874
Pettigrew's alive!
And he's right there!

1073
01:30:45,319 --> 01:30:49,710
-Me?! He's mental!
-Not you! Your rat!

1074
01:30:50,000 --> 01:30:52,992
-Scabbers has been in my family for--
-Twe|ve years?

1075
01:30:53,160 --> 01:30:55,549
Curiously long life
for a common garden rat!

1076
01:30:55,720 --> 01:30:58,188
-He's missing a toe. isn't he?
-So what?

1077
01:30:58,359 --> 01:31:01,192
-All they could find of Pettigrew was his--
-Finger!

1078
01:31:01,400 --> 01:31:04,517
Dirty coward cut it off
so everyone would think he was dead!

1079
01:31:04,680 --> 01:31:07,592
-And then he transformed into a rat!
-Show me.

1080
01:31:10,079 --> 01:31:13,037
-Give it to him. Ron.
-What are you trying to do to him?

1081
01:31:13,199 --> 01:31:14,234
Scabbers!

1082
01:31:14,400 --> 01:31:17,358
Leave him alone! Get off him!
What are you doing?

1083
01:31:38,920 --> 01:31:40,672
Remus?

1084
01:31:41,400 --> 01:31:42,833
Sirius.

1085
01:31:42,999 --> 01:31:44,830
My old friends!

1086
01:31:50,240 --> 01:31:53,915
Harry! Look at you.
You look so much like your father.

1087
01:31:54,079 --> 01:31:57,594
-James. We were the best of friends--
-How dare you speak to Harry!

1088
01:31:58,400 --> 01:32:00,914
How dare you talk about James
in front of him!

1089
01:32:01,120 --> 01:32:06,114
-You sold James and Lily to Voldemort!
-I didn't mean to!

1090
01:32:06,279 --> 01:32:08,998
The Dark Lord. You have no idea
the weapons he possesses!

1091
01:32:09,199 --> 01:32:11,713
Ask yourself. Sirius!
What would you have done?

1092
01:32:12,079 --> 01:32:17,437
-What would you have done?
-Died. rather than betray my friends!

1093
01:32:19,520 --> 01:32:21,795
James wouldn't have wanted
me killed!

1094
01:32:21,999 --> 01:32:27,437
Your dad would have spared me!
He would have shown me mercy!

1095
01:32:27,920 --> 01:32:31,913
Should have realized if Voldemort
didn't kill you. we would. Together!

1096
01:32:32,120 --> 01:32:34,076
No!

1097
01:32:35,520 --> 01:32:39,308
-Harry. this man--
-I know what he is.

1098
01:32:39,479 --> 01:32:41,310
But we'll take him to the castle.

1099
01:32:41,480 --> 01:32:46,315
-B|ess you. boy. Bless you!
-Get off!

1100
01:32:47,440 --> 01:32:49,715
I said we'd take you to the castle.

1101
01:32:50,079 --> 01:32:52,195
After that.
the dementors can have you.

1102
01:32:55,959 --> 01:32:59,554
Sorry about the bite.
I reckon that twinges a bit.

1103
01:32:59,719 --> 01:33:03,109
A bit? A bit?
You almost tore my leg off!

1104
01:33:03,280 --> 01:33:04,759
I was going for the rat.

1105
01:33:04,920 --> 01:33:08,595
Normally. I have a very sweet
disposition as a dog.

1106
01:33:08,760 --> 01:33:13,788
More than once. James suggested
that I make the change permanent.

1107
01:33:13,959 --> 01:33:18,635
The tail I could live with.
But the fleas. they're murder.

1108
01:33:30,679 --> 01:33:32,112
Okay.

1109
01:33:36,919 --> 01:33:39,353
-You better go.
-No. Don't worry. okay?

1110
01:33:39,519 --> 01:33:40,872
It's fine. I'll stay.

1111
01:33:41,599 --> 01:33:43,510
You go. I'll stay.

1112
01:33:43,800 --> 01:33:46,792
-You okay?
-|'m fine. Go.

1113
01:33:48,319 --> 01:33:51,197
-That looks really painful.
-So painful.

1114
01:33:51,360 --> 01:33:53,828
They might chop it.

1115
01:33:54,280 --> 01:33:56,840
I'm sure Madam Pomfrey
will fix it in a heartbeat.

1116
01:33:57,000 --> 01:34:01,039
It's too late. It's ruined.
It'll have to be chopped off.

1117
01:34:02,239 --> 01:34:03,991
It's beautiful. isn't it?

1118
01:34:04,800 --> 01:34:08,395
I'll never forget the first time
I walked through those doors.

1119
01:34:09,079 --> 01:34:12,116
It'll be nice to do it again
as a free man.

1120
01:34:14,160 --> 01:34:16,879
That was a noble thing
you did back there.

1121
01:34:17,640 --> 01:34:19,710
He doesn't deserve it.

1122
01:34:19,879 --> 01:34:22,916
I didn't think my dad
would have wanted his best friends...

1123
01:34:23,079 --> 01:34:24,558
...to become killers.

1124
01:34:24,719 --> 01:34:28,268
Besides. dead.
the truth dies with him.

1125
01:34:28,440 --> 01:34:30,715
Alive. you're free.

1126
01:34:30,879 --> 01:34:33,837
Turn me into a flobberworm.
Anything but the dementors!

1127
01:34:34,039 --> 01:34:37,236
Ron! Haven't I been a good pet?
You won't let them give me...

1128
01:34:37,399 --> 01:34:39,788
...to the dementors. will you?
I was your rat!

1129
01:34:39,959 --> 01:34:43,838
-Sweet. clever girl! Surely you won't--
-Get away from her!

1130
01:34:46,199 --> 01:34:48,030
I don't know if you know. Harry...

1131
01:34:48,199 --> 01:34:52,112
...but when you were born. James
and Lily made me your godfather.

1132
01:34:52,279 --> 01:34:54,156
I know.

1133
01:34:55,279 --> 01:34:59,158
I can understand if you choose
to stay with your aunt and uncle...

1134
01:34:59,319 --> 01:35:01,708
...but if you ever wanted
a different home....

1135
01:35:01,879 --> 01:35:04,268
What? Come and live with you?

1136
01:35:05,520 --> 01:35:08,557
It's just a thought.
I can understand if you don't want to.

1137
01:35:08,760 --> 01:35:10,239
Harry!

1138
01:35:25,039 --> 01:35:28,554
Remus. my old friend.
Have you taken your potion tonight?

1139
01:35:29,839 --> 01:35:34,959
You know the man you truly are. Remus!
This heart is where you truly live! Here!

1140
01:35:36,240 --> 01:35:38,151
This flesh is only flesh!

1141
01:35:39,280 --> 01:35:41,271
Exp elliarm us!

1142
01:35:50,960 --> 01:35:52,439
Harry!

1143
01:35:53,479 --> 01:35:56,312
Remus! Remus!

1144
01:36:02,280 --> 01:36:04,510
Run! Run!

1145
01:36:14,119 --> 01:36:16,075
-Come on.
-Wait. Wait.

1146
01:36:16,239 --> 01:36:21,108
Hermione! Bad idea. Bad idea.

1147
01:36:21,280 --> 01:36:23,430
Professor?

1148
01:36:27,360 --> 01:36:28,839
Professor Lupin?

1149
01:36:36,280 --> 01:36:39,397
Nice doggy. Nice doggy!

1150
01:36:39,799 --> 01:36:42,233
There you are. Potter!

1151
01:37:14,640 --> 01:37:15,629
Sirius!

1152
01:37:16,440 --> 01:37:18,749
Come back here. Potter!

1153
01:38:21,880 --> 01:38:23,233
Sirius!

1154
01:38:23,999 --> 01:38:26,832
No. Sirius!

1155
01:39:07,000 --> 01:39:09,753
Expecto Patronuml

1156
01:41:17,120 --> 01:41:19,395
Harry?

1157
01:41:20,280 --> 01:41:22,555
I saw my dad.

1158
01:41:22,760 --> 01:41:24,239
What?

1159
01:41:24,439 --> 01:41:25,918
He sent the dementors away.

1160
01:41:26,080 --> 01:41:27,433
I saw him across the lake.

1161
01:41:27,600 --> 01:41:29,192
Harry. they've captured Sirius.

1162
01:41:29,399 --> 01:41:32,118
Any minute the dementors
are gonna perform the Kiss.

1163
01:41:32,280 --> 01:41:34,669
-They're gonna kill him?
-No. It's worse.

1164
01:41:34,880 --> 01:41:36,632
Much worse.

1165
01:41:36,799 --> 01:41:39,074
They're going to suck out his soul.

1166
01:41:40,720 --> 01:41:42,039
Headmaster. stop them.

1167
01:41:42,199 --> 01:41:45,430
-They've got the wrong man.
-|t's true. Sirius is innocent.

1168
01:41:45,600 --> 01:41:47,716
-|t's Scabbers who did it.
-Scabbers?

1169
01:41:47,879 --> 01:41:49,198
He's my rat. sir.

1170
01:41:49,600 --> 01:41:53,229
He's not really a rat. He was a rat.
He was my brother Percy's rat.

1171
01:41:53,439 --> 01:41:56,954
-But then they gave him an owl--
-The point is. we know the truth.

1172
01:41:57,159 --> 01:41:59,548
-Please believe us.
-I do. Miss Granger.

1173
01:41:59,759 --> 01:42:04,958
But the word of three 13-year-old
wizards will convince few others.

1174
01:42:07,919 --> 01:42:10,592
A child's voice.
however honest and true...

1175
01:42:10,760 --> 01:42:14,355
...is meaningless to those
who have forgotten how to listen.

1176
01:42:19,360 --> 01:42:21,794
Mysterious thing. time.

1177
01:42:22,919 --> 01:42:24,193
Powerful...

1178
01:42:24,359 --> 01:42:27,112
...and when meddled with.
dangerous.

1179
01:42:28,640 --> 01:42:32,110
Sirius Black is in the topmost
cell of the Dark Tower.

1180
01:42:32,879 --> 01:42:34,915
You know the laws. Miss Granger.

1181
01:42:35,080 --> 01:42:36,798
You must not be seen.

1182
01:42:36,959 --> 01:42:40,474
And you would do well. I feel.
to return before this last chime.

1183
01:42:40,640 --> 01:42:44,030
If not. the consequences
are too ghastly to discuss.

1184
01:42:44,559 --> 01:42:46,277
If you succeed tonight...

1185
01:42:46,439 --> 01:42:49,158
...more than one innocent life
may be spared.

1186
01:42:50,919 --> 01:42:53,035
Three turns should do it. I think.

1187
01:42:57,719 --> 01:42:59,471
Oh. and by the way.

1188
01:42:59,639 --> 01:43:05,236
When in doubt. I find retracing
my steps to be a wise place to begin.

1189
01:43:05,400 --> 01:43:07,391
Good luck.

1190
01:43:07,880 --> 01:43:10,235
What the bloody hell
was that all about?

1191
01:43:10,880 --> 01:43:13,110
Sorry. Ron. but seeing
as you can't walk....

1192
01:43:40,919 --> 01:43:42,477
What just happened?

1193
01:43:42,640 --> 01:43:44,835
-Where's Ron?
-7:30.

1194
01:43:45,000 --> 01:43:46,797
Where were we at 7:30?

1195
01:43:46,960 --> 01:43:48,678
I don't know. Going to Hagrid's?

1196
01:43:48,839 --> 01:43:51,114
Come on. And we can't be seen.

1197
01:43:52,159 --> 01:43:53,911
Hermione!

1198
01:44:11,359 --> 01:44:13,919
Hermione! Hermione. wait.

1199
01:44:15,640 --> 01:44:19,076
Hermione. will you please tell me
what it is we're doing?

1200
01:44:19,280 --> 01:44:21,999
You foul. loathsome.
evil little cockroach!

1201
01:44:22,159 --> 01:44:23,433
That's us.

1202
01:44:23,639 --> 01:44:26,437
Hermione. no! He's not worth it.

1203
01:44:26,639 --> 01:44:28,038
This is not normal.

1204
01:44:30,239 --> 01:44:32,514
This is a Time-Turner. Harry.

1205
01:44:32,679 --> 01:44:34,795
McGonagall gave it to me first term.

1206
01:44:34,960 --> 01:44:38,157
This is how I've been getting
to my lessons all year.

1207
01:44:38,360 --> 01:44:41,432
-You mean we've gone back in time?
-Yes.

1208
01:44:41,599 --> 01:44:44,830
Dumbledore obviously wanted us
to return to this moment.

1209
01:44:47,039 --> 01:44:50,076
Clearly. something happened
he wants us to change.

1210
01:44:53,080 --> 01:44:54,354
Good punch.

1211
01:44:54,520 --> 01:44:55,953
Thanks.

1212
01:44:56,919 --> 01:44:58,511
Malfoy's coming.

1213
01:44:59,399 --> 01:45:01,629
-Run.
-Not a word to anyone. understood?

1214
01:45:02,080 --> 01:45:05,038
I'm gonna get that jumped-up
mudblood! Mark my words.

1215
01:45:05,200 --> 01:45:08,954
-That felt good.
-Not good. brilliant.

1216
01:45:10,280 --> 01:45:12,748
Come on. We should be at Hagrid's.

1217
01:45:31,120 --> 01:45:33,554
Look. Buckbeak's still alive.

1218
01:45:34,960 --> 01:45:36,757
Of course.

1219
01:45:36,919 --> 01:45:38,830
Remember what Dumbledore said?

1220
01:45:38,999 --> 01:45:42,878
If we succeed. more than one
innocent life could be spared.

1221
01:45:43,240 --> 01:45:44,514
Let's go.

1222
01:46:04,919 --> 01:46:06,955
Here they come. I'd better hurry.

1223
01:46:07,120 --> 01:46:09,509
Fudge has to see Buckbeak
before we steal him.

1224
01:46:09,679 --> 01:46:12,034
Otherwise. he'll think Hagrid
set him free.

1225
01:46:13,039 --> 01:46:15,314
Scabbers. you're alive!

1226
01:46:15,480 --> 01:46:18,153
-Keep a closer eye on your pet.
-That's Pettigrew.

1227
01:46:18,359 --> 01:46:21,157
-Harry. you can't.
-He betrayed my parents.

1228
01:46:21,319 --> 01:46:24,197
-You don't expect me to sit here.
-Yes. and you must!

1229
01:46:27,919 --> 01:46:30,513
Harry. you're in Hagrid's hut now.

1230
01:46:30,679 --> 01:46:33,398
If you go bursting in.
you'll think you've gone mad.

1231
01:46:33,559 --> 01:46:36,312
Awful things happen to wizards
who meddle with time.

1232
01:46:36,480 --> 01:46:38,630
We can't be seen.

1233
01:46:41,799 --> 01:46:43,437
Fudge is coming.

1234
01:46:44,319 --> 01:46:46,310
And we aren't leaving?

1235
01:46:48,400 --> 01:46:49,913
Why aren't we leaving?

1236
01:47:00,400 --> 01:47:01,879
Are you mad?

1237
01:47:07,639 --> 01:47:08,958
That hurt.

1238
01:47:09,160 --> 01:47:10,434
Sorry.

1239
01:47:30,439 --> 01:47:32,999
We're coming out the back door. Go!

1240
01:47:49,680 --> 01:47:52,399
Is that really what my hair
looks like from the back?

1241
01:47:54,359 --> 01:47:55,633
What?

1242
01:47:56,479 --> 01:47:58,231
I thought I just saw....

1243
01:47:58,439 --> 01:48:00,999
-Never mind.
-Let's go.

1244
01:48:14,719 --> 01:48:16,914
Okay. go. Harry. Go!

1245
01:48:22,919 --> 01:48:24,796
Get away. Get off.

1246
01:48:46,079 --> 01:48:49,355
Minister. I really think
I should sign as well.

1247
01:48:50,159 --> 01:48:53,196
Yes. very well. Perhaps it would be....

1248
01:48:53,399 --> 01:48:57,028
Okay. Buckbeak. Come quickly.
Come with us now. Come on.

1249
01:49:01,319 --> 01:49:03,913
Keep trying. Come on. Ouickly.

1250
01:49:06,200 --> 01:49:09,829
Buckbeak. Okay?
Ouickly. Hurry up. Okay?

1251
01:49:10,639 --> 01:49:13,790
-Your name only.
-|t's such a very long name....

1252
01:49:14,159 --> 01:49:15,797
Hurry up now. Buckbeak. okay?

1253
01:49:18,400 --> 01:49:21,233
Come on.
Come on. Buckbeak.

1254
01:49:21,439 --> 01:49:23,634
Come and get the nice dead ferret.

1255
01:49:26,159 --> 01:49:30,471
-Come on. It's here. Come on. Beaky.
-Here we are. minister. Follow me.

1256
01:49:30,679 --> 01:49:32,271
-Now. look there.
-Where?

1257
01:49:32,479 --> 01:49:35,710
-Look beyond the rocks.
-What am I supposed to see?

1258
01:49:35,880 --> 01:49:39,236
Professor Dippet had that ling
planted when he was headmaster.

1259
01:49:39,400 --> 01:49:42,119
-Oh. yes. Indeed. indeed.
-And all the strawberries.

1260
01:49:43,040 --> 01:49:45,793
-Come on. Buckbeak. Come on.
-| see no strawberries.

1261
01:49:45,959 --> 01:49:47,074
-Over there.
-Where?

1262
01:49:47,239 --> 01:49:48,911
-Over there.
-This way.

1263
01:49:49,119 --> 01:49:51,679
-Let's get this over. please.
-All right.

1264
01:49:53,280 --> 01:49:54,918
But where is it?

1265
01:49:55,800 --> 01:49:57,916
I saw the beast. just now.

1266
01:49:58,519 --> 01:50:00,635
-Not a moment ago!
-How extraordinary.

1267
01:50:00,800 --> 01:50:02,074
Buckbeak.

1268
01:50:02,279 --> 01:50:06,192
Come now. Dumbledore.
Someone's obviously released him.

1269
01:50:06,359 --> 01:50:07,633
-Hagrid?
-Buckbeak.

1270
01:50:07,840 --> 01:50:11,913
I don't think the minister's suggesting
you had anything to do with this.

1271
01:50:12,119 --> 01:50:14,838
How could you?
You've been with us all the time.

1272
01:50:15,000 --> 01:50:16,797
-Right.
-Well. well.

1273
01:50:16,960 --> 01:50:18,439
We must search the grounds.

1274
01:50:18,599 --> 01:50:21,511
Well. search the skies.
if you must. minister.

1275
01:50:21,679 --> 01:50:26,878
Meanwhile. I'd like a nice cup
of tea or a large brandy.

1276
01:50:27,040 --> 01:50:30,874
Oh. executioner. your services
are no longer required.

1277
01:50:31,039 --> 01:50:32,836
Thank you.

1278
01:50:33,040 --> 01:50:36,191
You'll find no small glasses
in this house. professor.

1279
01:50:46,519 --> 01:50:47,952
-Come on.
-This way.

1280
01:50:54,480 --> 01:50:56,198
This way. now.

1281
01:50:58,519 --> 01:51:00,191
-Now what?
-We save Sirius.

1282
01:51:00,399 --> 01:51:02,788
-How?
-No idea.

1283
01:51:11,719 --> 01:51:13,994
-Look. It's Lupin.
-Immohulusl

1284
01:51:20,160 --> 01:51:22,071
And Snape's coming.

1285
01:51:28,040 --> 01:51:29,632
And now we wait.

1286
01:51:30,800 --> 01:51:32,518
And now we wait.

1287
01:51:58,960 --> 01:52:02,077
-At least someone's enjoying himself.
-Yeah.

1288
01:52:04,760 --> 01:52:06,478
-Hermione?
-Yeah?

1289
01:52:06,639 --> 01:52:10,791
Before. down by the lake.
when I was with Sirius...

1290
01:52:10,960 --> 01:52:12,996
...I did see someone.

1291
01:52:13,159 --> 01:52:16,435
That someone
made the dementors go away.

1292
01:52:16,599 --> 01:52:17,873
With a Patronus.

1293
01:52:18,039 --> 01:52:19,870
I heard Snape telling Dumbledore.

1294
01:52:20,040 --> 01:52:21,439
According to him...

1295
01:52:21,599 --> 01:52:24,875
...only a really powerful wizard
could have conjured it.

1296
01:52:25,040 --> 01:52:26,837
It was my dad.

1297
01:52:27,919 --> 01:52:29,637
My dad conjured the Patronus.

1298
01:52:29,799 --> 01:52:31,949
-Harry. but your dad's--
-Dead. I know.

1299
01:52:33,319 --> 01:52:35,549
I'm just telling you what I saw.

1300
01:52:39,520 --> 01:52:41,078
Here we come.

1301
01:52:46,519 --> 01:52:48,794
You see Sirius talking to me there?

1302
01:52:48,960 --> 01:52:51,679
-He's asking me to come live with him.
-That's great.

1303
01:52:51,840 --> 01:52:55,037
When we free him. I'll never
have to go back to the Dursleys'.

1304
01:52:55,199 --> 01:52:56,757
It'll just be me and him.

1305
01:52:57,399 --> 01:52:59,276
We could live in the country...

1306
01:52:59,439 --> 01:53:01,953
...someplace you can see the sky.

1307
01:53:02,119 --> 01:53:04,838
He'll like that after
all those years in Azkaban.

1308
01:53:05,840 --> 01:53:07,319
Harry!

1309
01:53:08,799 --> 01:53:10,437
Run!

1310
01:53:17,040 --> 01:53:18,519
Let's go.

1311
01:53:37,279 --> 01:53:39,509
-What are you doing?
-Saving your life.

1312
01:53:43,599 --> 01:53:44,918
Thanks.

1313
01:53:46,680 --> 01:53:50,559
-Great. Now he's coming for us.
-Yeah. I didn't think about that. Run!

1314
01:55:02,599 --> 01:55:04,271
That was so scary.

1315
01:55:04,439 --> 01:55:07,272
Poor Professor Lupin's
having a really tough night.

1316
01:55:18,240 --> 01:55:21,232
Sirius. Come on!

1317
01:55:36,599 --> 01:55:38,635
-This is horrible.
-Don't worry.

1318
01:55:38,799 --> 01:55:41,871
My dad will come.
He'll conjure the Patronus.

1319
01:55:50,240 --> 01:55:51,992
Any minute now.

1320
01:55:52,200 --> 01:55:54,156
Right there. You'll see.

1321
01:55:55,480 --> 01:55:57,869
Harry. listen to me.
No one's coming.

1322
01:55:58,040 --> 01:56:00,474
Don't worry. he will.
He will come.

1323
01:56:04,440 --> 01:56:06,795
-Sirius.
-You're dying...

1324
01:56:08,759 --> 01:56:10,556
...both of you.

1325
01:56:12,560 --> 01:56:14,198
Harry!

1326
01:56:16,040 --> 01:56:19,749
Expecto Patronuml

1327
01:57:15,959 --> 01:57:17,472
You were right. Hermione.

1328
01:57:17,639 --> 01:57:20,836
It wasn't my dad I saw earlier.
It was me!

1329
01:57:21,000 --> 01:57:23,639
I saw myself conjuring
the Patronus before.

1330
01:57:23,799 --> 01:57:26,074
I knew I could do it
this time because...

1331
01:57:26,240 --> 01:57:27,878
...well. I had already done it.

1332
01:57:28,040 --> 01:57:30,395
-Does that make sense?
-No.

1333
01:57:30,560 --> 01:57:33,279
But I don't like flying...!

1334
01:57:45,879 --> 01:57:47,153
Bombardal

1335
01:58:19,119 --> 01:58:21,792
I'll be forever grateful for this...

1336
01:58:21,959 --> 01:58:23,233
...to both of you.

1337
01:58:23,399 --> 01:58:26,197
-I want to go with you.
-One day. perhaps.

1338
01:58:26,359 --> 01:58:29,157
For some time. my life
will be too unpredictable.

1339
01:58:29,320 --> 01:58:30,992
And besides...

1340
01:58:31,880 --> 01:58:35,031
-...you're meant to be here.
-But you're innocent.

1341
01:58:35,199 --> 01:58:37,235
And you know it.

1342
01:58:38,280 --> 01:58:40,077
And for now. that will do.

1343
01:58:42,320 --> 01:58:44,754
I expect you're tired of hearing this...

1344
01:58:45,719 --> 01:58:48,153
...but you look so like your father.

1345
01:58:49,840 --> 01:58:51,717
Except your eyes.

1346
01:58:52,640 --> 01:58:54,835
-You have--
-My mother's eyes.

1347
01:58:56,719 --> 01:59:01,588
It's cruel that I spent so much time
with James and Lily. and you so little.

1348
01:59:02,159 --> 01:59:03,592
But know this:

1349
01:59:04,680 --> 01:59:07,717
The ones that love us
never really leave us.

1350
01:59:09,039 --> 01:59:10,916
And you can always find them...

1351
01:59:13,199 --> 01:59:14,996
...in here.

1352
01:59:24,959 --> 01:59:27,393
You really are the brightest
witch of your age.

1353
01:59:53,119 --> 01:59:54,677
We have to go.

1354
02:00:21,800 --> 02:00:24,360
-We||?
-He's free. We did it.

1355
02:00:24,520 --> 02:00:25,999
Did what?

1356
02:00:26,159 --> 02:00:28,036
Good night.

1357
02:00:36,440 --> 02:00:37,714
How did you get there?

1358
02:00:37,880 --> 02:00:40,440
I was talking to you there.
And now you're there.

1359
02:00:40,760 --> 02:00:43,274
-What's he talking about. Harry?
-I don't know.

1360
02:00:43,440 --> 02:00:46,830
Honestly. Ron. How can somebody
be in two places at once?

1361
02:01:12,239 --> 02:01:13,672
Hello. Harry.

1362
02:01:17,159 --> 02:01:18,911
I saw you coming.

1363
02:01:23,279 --> 02:01:25,873
I've looked worse. believe me.

1364
02:01:28,480 --> 02:01:31,517
-You've been sacked.
-No.

1365
02:01:31,679 --> 02:01:34,512
No. I resigned. actually.

1366
02:01:34,679 --> 02:01:36,397
Resigned? Why?

1367
02:01:36,560 --> 02:01:41,634
Well. it seems that somebody
let slip the nature of my condition.

1368
02:01:41,800 --> 02:01:47,079
This time tomorrow. the owls will start
arriving and parents will not want...

1369
02:01:47,239 --> 02:01:50,470
...well. someone like me
teaching their children.

1370
02:01:50,680 --> 02:01:52,511
-But Dumbledore--
-He has already...

1371
02:01:52,679 --> 02:01:54,476
...risked enough on my behalf.

1372
02:01:54,639 --> 02:01:57,756
Besides. people like me are....

1373
02:01:58,359 --> 02:02:01,556
Well. let's just say
that I'm used to it by now.

1374
02:02:10,719 --> 02:02:13,187
Why do you look so miserable. Harry?

1375
02:02:13,359 --> 02:02:15,429
None of it made any difference.

1376
02:02:15,599 --> 02:02:18,989
-Pettigrew escaped.
-Didn't make any difference?

1377
02:02:19,160 --> 02:02:22,516
It made all the difference in the world.
You uncovered the truth.

1378
02:02:22,679 --> 02:02:25,068
You saved an innocent man
from a terrible fate.

1379
02:02:25,440 --> 02:02:27,829
It made a great deal of difference.

1380
02:02:32,279 --> 02:02:34,395
If I am proud of anything...

1381
02:02:34,560 --> 02:02:37,120
...it is of how much
you have learned this year.

1382
02:02:37,280 --> 02:02:39,919
Now. since I am no longer
your teacher...

1383
02:02:40,080 --> 02:02:44,153
...I feel no guilt whatsoever
about giving this back to you.

1384
02:02:45,040 --> 02:02:47,429
So now I'll say goodbye. Harry.

1385
02:02:47,600 --> 02:02:50,068
I feel sure we'll meet again sometime.

1386
02:02:50,599 --> 02:02:51,873
Until then...

1387
02:02:53,160 --> 02:02:54,798
...mischief managed.

1388
02:03:27,639 --> 02:03:31,678
Stand back. I said! Or I'll take it
upstairs if you don't settle.

1389
02:03:31,840 --> 02:03:33,193
Harry.

1390
02:03:33,999 --> 02:03:35,318
Wherever did you get it?

1391
02:03:35,479 --> 02:03:37,788
Can I have a go. Harry?
After you. of course.

1392
02:03:37,959 --> 02:03:40,029
-What are you talking about?
-Ouiet.

1393
02:03:40,199 --> 02:03:43,350
Let the man through.
I didn't mean to open it. Harry.

1394
02:03:43,520 --> 02:03:45,909
It was badly wrapped.
They made me do it.

1395
02:03:46,080 --> 02:03:47,513
Did not.

1396
02:03:48,840 --> 02:03:52,196
-|t's a Firebolt.
-|t's the fastest broom in the world.

1397
02:03:52,359 --> 02:03:53,838
For me?

1398
02:03:54,000 --> 02:03:56,434
-But who sent it?
-No one knows.

1399
02:03:56,599 --> 02:03:58,430
This came with it.

1400
02:04:03,080 --> 02:04:04,672
-Go on. Harry!
-Yeah. let's see.

1401
02:04:04,839 --> 02:04:06,591
How fast is it. Harry?

1402
02:04:25,160 --> 02:04:26,718
Lumos.

1403
02:04:26,880 --> 02:04:29,189
I solemnly swear that I am
up to no good.

1404
02:15:20,559 --> 02:15:22,277
Mischief managed.

1405
02:15:27,799 --> 02:15:29,198
Nox.

